title: Virus
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2Qma2dN

by Lackless

Dan is a hacker, living alone, scraping a living doing bits of code for pay, when he finds an old piece of tech in a dumpster that will change the way he looks at the world.

He moves some of the pile of crap, digging around for the source of the blue flash. There, underneath an old headset, he finds an older model jack, kind of bulky and unfashionable looking. He frowns at it turning it over in his hand. Even by the time he’d had his implants fitted a year ago this model had already become outdated. How was it here now and how was it still holding a charge? Had someone been wearing it until recently? He looks around but there is no-one to be seen. He’s in an alley, surely he would have noticed someone coming the other way? On a whim, he pops the obsolete jack behind his right ear and slips into v-space.

summary: I believe Dan and Phil when they say that Phil is fine and he was just exhausted. If we didn’t know that and if something VERY...
body:
I believe Dan and Phil when they say that Phil is fine and he was just exhausted. If we didn’t know that and if something VERY SERIOUS was going on, I wouldn’t have made any jokes. However there is absolutely no need to freak out whether or not Phil is okay. He fainted, went to the hospital, was released after some testing, and is now fine. We’ve gotten a few confirmations of that.

Just the fact that they were being goofy is enough to show that we have NO NEED to be freaked out about ANYTHING. If something serious was going on, they most likely wouldn’t have shared it with us. So to everyone making a big deal out of nothing; stop. Just breathe. Not everything has to be serious and treated as a PSA.

summary: I’ve seen so many posts the last day are so that are like “lol why did Phil even go to the hospital, he just fainted, I faint 12...
body:
I’ve seen so many posts the last day are so that are like “lol why did Phil even go to the hospital, he just fainted, I faint 12 times a day every day, fainting just happens sometimes it’s not a big deal.”


So, as a grown adult with years of first aid training, five years experience in emergency services, and three years experience in nursing, let me tell you this:


Fainting isn’t fucking normal.


Sure, it’s generally pretty harmless. The majority of the time, it’s caused by something like low blood sugar, dehydration, low blood pressure, or exhaustion. None of which are typically serious issues on their own, and can be fixed pretty easily.


HOWEVER


If you faint out of the blue, if it’s never happened before, if you have no diagnosis that would cause fainting spells, then you should go to the fucking doctor. If you faint regularly, and have no idea what’s causing it, you should go to the fucking doctor.


Fainting spells are typically not much cause for concern, but they can be a symptom of something bigger, and more serious. So yes, while fainting does sometimes “just happen”, that doesn’t mean it’s normal, and it doesn’t mean you should just ignore it.

body:
Phandom get a grip….

Phil has been in the hospital. We don’t know the cause. We can only hope he’s doing all right now.

While it’s indeed moving that Dan is there with him in whatever capacity, let’s keep Phangirling at back of our minds and wish Phil a speedy recovery.

I am a bit disheartened that fanfic prompts and naughty jokes, etc is being circulated with this event. Yeah we ship the boys till kingdom comes, but now ain’t the time . Get a grip okay. While it’s very tempting and all, don’t use it for Phan proof.

I am a bit disheartened that fanfic prompts and naughty jokes, etc is being circulated with this event. Yeah we ship the boys till kingdom comes, but now ain’t the time . Get a grip okay. While it’s very tempting and all, don’t use it for Phan proof.
